                    "analysis": "This binary is a variant of the Xorist ransomware family. It exhibits classic ransomware behaviors including recursive file enumeration across logical drives, file encryption using a custom XOR-based routine, and renaming affected files. It establishes persistence via the 'Alcmeter' Registry Run key and displays a ransom interface ('0p3nSOurc3 X0r157') demanding a password for decryption. It also features a self-deletion mechanism using a batch command and changes the system wallpaper to a ransom notification. Relevant IOCs include the 'HOW TO DECRYPT FILES.txt' ransom note and the 'Alcmeter' registry value.",
